dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Iraklion, sheet G-20. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4410)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4410. Alternate title: Iraklion (Candia). Transverse Mercator projection. Principal meridians are Athens and Greenwich. Universal transverse Mercator and Crete zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints andair information deleted by AMS, 1948. Relief shown by 100 and 200 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Transliteration from the Greek is according to R.G.S.II (revised) system. Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1943. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1948.
